{"word":"κίνησις","slug":"κίνησις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κίνησις</b></el> <el>(κί¯νησις, εως) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κινέω'><el>κινέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>movement, motion</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <i>a dance</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>movement</i>, in a political sense, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; of the Peloponn. war, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}